messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /printdocument/{id}

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD acceptable: false

- POST acceptable: false

- OPTIONS acceptable: false

- TRACE acceptable: false

- GET acceptable: true

- PUT acceptable: false

- DELETE acceptable: false

- PATCH acceptable: false

Explanation:
- The getDocument method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printdocument/{id}", method = RequestMethod.GET). There is no class-level @RequestMapping on PrintRequestController that would add a prefix, so the full path is exactly "/printdocument/{id}".
- The method attribute explicitly restricts the mapping to RequestMethod.GET. Therefore only GET is acceptable according to the code.
- Per the instruction to base acceptability on the code (not on framework runtime behavior or implicit allowances), methods other than the explicitly declared GET (including HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) are considered not acceptable.
